            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.31.28-29_0001a" />
               <note type="curatorial">126-2</note>
               <note type="clerical">[M Feb 9 61 
                                        2:30pm]</note> 
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                Next Day!
                2-8-'61	
                    </dateline>
                
                <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Yesterday I heard that Atherton had a heart attack a week ago. So I called his home and he answered, having just returned from the hospital. He told me that he was doing well and felt hopeful; that the doctor said he could return to his classes next Tuesday (Feb. 14). He gave me the impression that the attack was a moderate one, <hi rend="underline">if there be such</hi>.
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.31.28-29_0001b"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>           <note type="curatorial">Aly Collection</note>
                    
                    He said <del/> that when he was around again we'd get together for the final arrangements regarding the <hi rend="caps">MSS</hi> and the library.</p>
                
                <p>By the way, Lady, <hi rend="underline">did</hi> I tell you in my letter of yesterday about the "poem" "To a Hat-Pin" which was published in <hi rend="italic">Truth</hi> during 1901 or -02? I was obliged to copy the last fold of the letter, and I'm wondering if I <hi rend="underline">missed</hi> a page!</p>
               
                <p>Affectionate hellos to Bower, Stewart, you &#8212; and our <hi rend="underline">arful</hi> <add><note type="authorial">(See over)</note></add> little friend.</p> <closer><signed>John</signed></closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">28</fw>
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.31.28-29_0002"/>
                
                    <postscript><p>How does Webster spell <hi rend="underline">arful</hi> -arffull? Maybe Perky knows.</p> <closer><signed>Jno.</signed></closer></postscript>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            
